  <h2>Jessica Ferrow</h2><p class=""><strong>Co-Founder of Twelve Consulting</strong></p><p class="">Jessica is the co-founder of climate impact agency <a href="http://www.twelvefutures.com/" target="_blank">Twelve</a>, which helps businesses respond to the climate and ecological crisis. She has spent more than twelve years working with purpose-driven businesses and B Corps on their sustainability strategies and communications. As well as being a climate activist, nature facilitator and podcaster, Jessica is a mentor and advisory board member of <a href="https://catalysechange.com/" target="_blank">Catalyse Change</a> , a social enterprise helping young women into sustainability careers. She is also a non-executive director of the <a href="http://www.bristolgreencapital.org/" target="_blank">Bristol Green Capital Partnership</a> , co-chair of the <a href="https://bristolgreencapital.org/the-partnership-launches-climate-leaders-group/" target="_blank">Bristol Climate Leaders Group</a> and sits on Bristol’s <a href="https://www.bristolonecity.com/environment/" target="_blank">One City Environment Board</a> , helping the city achieve its goal to be net zero by 2030.</p><p class=""><a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/footprint-futures/id1528620398" target="_blank">Apple Podcast</a></p><p class=""><a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/0AVBPat98sSQuytbhheSxB" target="_blank">Spotify</a></p><p class="">In this episode of the Footprint Futures podcast we talk with Jessica Ferrow, co-founder of Twelve Agency, on driving sustainability strategy and communication.</p><p class="">During the episode we approach: </p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">How to drive sustainability for businesses</p></li><li><p class="">The importance of setting the right strategy</p></li><li><p class="">How to make help businesses to communicate their sustainability efforts with the most transparency</p></li><li><p class="">How businesses need to transform in order to become more sustainable.</p></li></ul><h3>Footprint Futures is the podcast where we interview forward-thinking ecopreneurs and change-makers on how to accelerate the world towards a sustainable future.</h3>]]></content:encoded><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/646f9bfe5c10277d6cd432c7/28dbc243-235e-40a1-a3fe-43833cd3deeb/8e920-frame701.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="1500"><media:title type="plain">Jessica Ferrow | Driving sustainability strategy and communication.</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Why sustainability creates business value.</title><category>Futures</category><dc:creator>Sebastian Gier</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 24 Feb 2022 14:36:42 +0000</pubDate><link>https://www.footprint-intelligence.com/blog/why-sustainability-creates-business-value</link><guid isPermaLink="false">646f9bfe5c10277d6cd432c7:64831b1c9bfe6002ab7095da:64831b379bfe6002ab709948</guid><description><![CDATA[The immediate need to address sustainability concerns is clear: the world 
